-- Halliburton seeks investors, eyes $80 bln in projects
-- 
-- Tue May 22, 2007 3:07am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/22/businesspro-halliburton-investments-dc-idUSL2222088220070522

 

 DUBAI  (Reuters) - Halliburton ( HAL.N ) said on Tuesday it 
was looking for major investors to take a long-term stake in 
its eastern hemisphere operation and is eyeing around $80 
billion in projects worldwide over the next five years. 

  "One of my goals would be to find a set of investors or 
investor interested in taking a longer-term investment in the 
company," Halliburton CEO Dave Lefar said, when asked if the 
global oil services firm was searching for major investors for 
its eastern hemisphere expansion.